Amer Sports Bulgaria Aims to Raise Output, Pari Says

-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   K o n s t a n t i n o v a
-- 
2011-03-10T16:33:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/amer-sports-bulgaria-eyes-20-share-of-skis-market-pari-reports.html
(Corrects profit to revenue in second paragraph of story
first published on March 8.)  The Bulgarian unit of  Amer Sports
Oyj (AMEAS) , the maker of Wilson tennis rackets and Salomon skis, plans
to produce 1 million pairs of skis, or 20 percent of the global
market by 2012,  Pari  reported.  The Chepelare, Bulgaria-based factory produced 730,000
pairs of skis in 2010 and aims to make 900,000 pairs this year,
the newspaper said, citing Krastyo Vangelov, the factoryâ€™s
manager. The unit had revenue of 50 million lev ($35 million) in
2010, Pari said.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
